mutant: m027_getrepo_http_fault_disabled
target: internal/simulator/http/faults.go
failure-mode: |
  The simulator's getRepo HTTP fault injection is silently disabled by a
  flipped comparator: the "no budget remaining" guard `st.remaining <= 0`
  becomes `st.remaining >= 0`, which is ALWAYS true (remaining starts
  positive and never goes negative), so maybeGetRepoHTTPFault always returns
  (0, false) and a scheduled 503 never fires (st.fired never increments).
  Models a regression that breaks the fault-injection subsystem itself — the
  anti-vacuity machinery every swarm-mode run relies on to prove its recovery
  paths were actually exercised.
expected-detection: |
  Killed by assertFaultPlanFired in TestOracle_DefaultLifecycle (swarm mode):
  the scheduled hot/secondary-DID getRepo 503s never fire, so
  UnfiredGetRepoHTTPFailures() is non-empty and the
  "configured getRepo HTTP faults must fire" assertion fails. This is the
  #105 proof that the fault-injection subsystem's own kill power is asserted
  by a mutant, not only by code reading. Default tier.
expected-tier: default
tiers: default,stress

